The favorable stability, highly PL performance and low riskiness of COQDs lay the foundation of intracellular sensing applications. As shown in Fig. S10, with pH increases, the blue fluorescence signals of Hela cells improve gradually, which suggests the well cell membrane penetration of COQDs. Compared with COQDs, the COQDs-Rh 6G complex sensing system is more superior due to the intuitive color changes. Therefore, we further carried out cell imaging experiments to achieve intracellular imaging of pH changes. Fig. 6
                         shows the images of cell imaging in different pH environments, with the pH increase from 6.0, 7.5 to 9.0, the fluorescence signal in the blue channel enhances sharply, while the signal of green channel decreases gradually. The obvious color change can be observed definitely by the naked eye (Fig. 7
                        ). All the above results indicated that the constructed COQDs-Rh 6G complex sensing system could monitor the pH fluctuation in living cells effectively.
